      "@type": "behavioral:SeedInsufficiency",
      "name": "runtime-code-diverges-from-seed",
      "insufficiency:text": "The behavioral-seed program states that runtime code (src/behavioral/behavioral.ts) is supporting implementation evidence, not ontology authority. However, behavioral.ts contains specific implementation details (Object.hasOwn for isPlaitedTrigger detection, Symbol-based thread naming for trigger threads, queueMicrotask in trigger implementation, generator.return() for interrupt, Object.freeze on the public API) that are not reflected in the behavioral-seed anchors. The seed provides behavioral semantics but the runtime has additional implementation specificity.",
